			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since you make a lot of plugins, i've added a URL-alias on the IGN central for your site, meaning all bots can reach your site with ex:
<br />

<br />
/tell theirbot net koi
<br />

<br />
the central URL-alias will lead to: "http://www.hot.ee/bond4u/ao/ign/"
<br />

<br />
the ingame IGN "index" pages are called "mainpage.txt"
<br />

<br />
so if you put up a info, with dynavars or AO-tags etc on <a href="http://www.hot.ee/bond4u/ao/ign/mainpage.txt" target="_blank">http://www.hot.ee/bond4u/ao/ign/mainpage.txt</a>
<br />

<br />
then people will see that page ingame when they
<br />
do
<br />

<br />
/tell theirbot net koi
<br />

<br />
if you put your plugins there, those bots connected to central can also download your plugins with ex:
<br />

<br />
/tell theirbot get koi/filename.pack
<br />

<br />
etc.
<br />

<br />
here is an example of a ingame "index" file:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">
<br />
