<br />

<br />
You can also use dynavars to include dynamic sub-pages, ex
<br />

<br />
(url)(alias)(word3).txt(/url)
<br />

<br />
would fetch and include the text from <a href="http://www.hot.ee/bond4u/ao/ign/.$word3.txt" target="_blank">http://www.hot.ee/bond4u/ao/ign/.$word3.txt</a>
<br />

<br />
in an example, if i did:
<br />

<br />
/tell mybot net koi about &lt;---
<br />

<br />
it would then fetch mainpage.txt, and include the text in:
<br />
<a href="http://www.hot.ee/bond4u/ao/ign/about.txt" target="_blank">http://www.hot.ee/bond4u/ao/ign/about.txt</a> to be shown instead of the placeholder on mainpage.txt.
<br />

<br />
you can also ex add dynamic content based on the dimension, sender profession, level etc. ex:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">
<br />
Hi there, welcome to my &#40;sender-prof&#41; menu&#58;
<br />

<br />
&#40;url&#41;&#40;alias&#41;&#40;sender-prof&#41;.txt&#40;/url&#41;
<br />

<br />
thank you</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
would include the text from ex doctor.txt if if my character were a doctor when triggering the command /tell mybot net koi
<br />

<br />
etc.
<br />

<br />
PS: The central URL-alias list updates on the bots only once an hour or when bot is relogged/restarted.
<br />

<br />
You can also make a items-database online that way, as it can include php files aswell and will then include the output into the textfile when shown ingame.
<br />

<br />
ex of mainpage.txt working as a url-based itemdb:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">
<br />
you searched for &#40;word3&#41;&#58;
<br />

<br />
found&#58;
<br />
&#40;url&#41;&#40;alias&#41;itemfinder.php?item=&#40;word3&#41;&#40;/url&#41;
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
whatever your itemfinder.php responds with and spits out as a result, would then be shown as a result in the window ingame. That way you can make complex "central" plugins with full php-functionality spitting out results back to the user based on their input.
<br />

<br />
the (url) &lt;-- dynavar can also include from any url/site, not just the site the host text/info file is resided. ex, you can have your ingame site spit out rds feeds from news-sites other places etc.
<br />

<br />
Amona</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
